        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 12:40PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1240 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Donner Peak, or near Olympic Valley. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alpine Meadows, Prosser Creek Reservoir, Tahoe City, Olympic Valley,
Northstar, Donner Peak, Truckee, Northstar Ski Area, Granite Flat
Campground, Lakeside Campground, Ca 89 At Placer-Nevada Co Line,
Olympic Valley Ski Area, Dollar Point, Alpine Meadows Campground,
Tahoe State Rec Area Campground, Truckee-Tahoe Airport, Silver Creek
Campground, Donner Memorial Campground, and Sunnyside-Tahoe City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
